The regex expression to extract a three character code like "1Jn" from a filename in format "57-1Jn.usfm" would be:

```regex
(?<=-\w{3}\.)\w{3}
```

Explanation of the regex pattern:

- `(?<=-\w{3}\.)`: Positive lookbehind to match a hyphen followed by three word characters (letters or digits) and a dot.
- `\w{3}`: Matches exactly three word characters (letters or digits).

So, this regex pattern will match the three character code "1Jn" from the given filename format "57-1Jn.usfm".
